title: Top Places to visit in Nashik, Maharashtra
content: Nashik is an ancient holy city in the northern region of the Indian state of Maharashtra. Situated on the banks of river Godavari, Nasik is well known for being one of Hindu pilgrimage sites, that of Kumbh Mela which is held every 12 years. It is the Third largest city in Maharashtra after Mumbai
